                        you can reach our on-call practitioner at:
                    </p>
                    <div class="emergency-contact">
                        <strong>Emergency Line: +1 (555) 123-4568</strong>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            {{!-- FAQ --}}
            <section class="appointment-faq">
                <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                <div class="faq-grid">
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <h3>How far in advance should I book?</h3>
                        <p>We recommend booking 1-2 weeks in advance for initial consultations, though we often have same-week availability.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <h3>What if I need to cancel or reschedule?</h3>
                        <p>Please give us at least 24 hours notice for cancellations or rescheduling to avoid any fees.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <h3>Do you offer virtual consultations?</h3>
                        <p>Yes, we offer telemedicine appointments for follow-up visits and certain types of consultations.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <h3>Can I bring my child to the appointment?</h3>
                        <p>Absolutely! We welcome children and have a family-friendly environment. We also offer specialized pediatric consultations.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

        </div>
    </article>
